as_survival_curves() is a generic function for converting objects to the survival_curves class. There is currently only a method for a data.frame.

as_survival_curves(x, ...)

# S3 method for data.frame
as_survival_curves(x, time = "time", id = "id", survival = "survival", ...)

Arguments

x

An object of the appropriate class.
...

Additional arguments to pass to survival_curves().
time

The name of the column containing the times a which survival probabilities were computed.
id

The name of the column containing an indentifier for each individual.
survival

The name of the column containing survival probabilities.

# Create a data frame storing survival curves
N <- 3 # Number of individuals
times <- rep(seq(0, 30, 1/12))
rates = runif(N, .2, .5)

  id = rep(1:N, each = length(times)),
  time = rep(times, times = length(rates)),
  rate = rep(rates, each = length(times))
)

# Convert the data frame to a "survival_curves" object
